<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Chhattisgarh</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="state-details">
        <h2>Welcome to Chhattisgarh</h2>
        <p>Chhattisgarh is a state in central India known for its rich cultural heritage, natural beauty, and tribal traditions. It is often referred to as the "Rice Bowl of India" due to its agricultural importance.</p>

        <h3>Key Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Capital:</strong> Raipur</li>
            <li><strong>Official Language:</strong> Hindi</li>
            <li><strong>Major Festivals:</strong> Bastar Dussehra, Hareli Festival, Madai Festival</li>
            <li><strong>Specialty:</strong> Handicrafts, tribal jewelry, and rice-based delicacies</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Popular Tourist Attractions</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Chitrakote Falls:</strong> Known as the "Niagara Falls of India," it is a spectacular waterfall on the Indravati River.</li>
            <li><strong>Kanger Valley National Park:</strong> A paradise for nature lovers, it is home to rare wildlife and limestone caves.</li>
            <li><strong>Bastar Region:</strong> Famous for its vibrant tribal culture and unique handicrafts.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
